---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const books = [
  { slug: 'cribsheet',                       title: 'Cribsheet' },
  { slug: 'good-inside',                     title: 'Good Inside' },
  { slug: 'the-5-love-languages-of-teenagers', title: 'The 5 Love Languages of Teenagers' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Love Your Family — Personal Takeaways"
  description="Personal takeaways from the Love Your Family shelf: Cribsheet, Good Inside, and The 5 Love Languages of Teenagers."
>
  <a class="overlay-back" href="/">&#8592; Back to Bookshelf</a>
  <a class="overlay-close" href="/" aria-label="Close">&times;</a>

  <div class="takeaways-content">
    <span class="takeaways-tag">Love Your Family</span>
    <h1 class="takeaways-title">Love Your Family</h1>
    <p class="takeaways-author" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Personal Takeaways</p>

    <div style="display:flex; gap:0.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:2rem;">
      {books.map((b) => (
        <a href={`/books/${b.slug}/`} class="overlay-takeaways-btn" style="font-size:0.78rem; padding:0.35rem 0.9rem;">
          {b.title}
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="dd-topic-list" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#tk-digital-detox">Digital Detox</a>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="tk-digital-detox">
      <div class="tk-section-title">Digital Detox: Protecting Your Family's Attention</div>
      <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#5E554B;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:.75rem">The screens in your home are not neutral — they are precision-engineered to be as addictive as possible, built by some of the smartest people on earth with the sole goal of capturing your family's attention and never giving it back. Autoplay, infinite scroll, push notifications, and algorithmic rabbit holes don't happen by accident. They happen by design. And willpower alone is not a fair fight. The families winning this battle aren't more disciplined — they've simply built environmental guardrails that are stronger than the pull of the screen. I spent months researching every digital detox tool available and found that no single product closes every gap. Your home Wi-Fi, your personal devices on the road, and your phone itself all require different layers of coverage. The solution is a three-tool stack: one tool locks down the entire home network, one syncs blocks across your phones and computers wherever you are, and one enforces limits at the cellular level — so there's nowhere left to escape. What follows is a complete breakdown of each tool: what it can do, where it falls short, and how the three work together to give your family back the one thing no algorithm can manufacture — presence.</p>
      <a class="go-deeper-btn" href="/love-your-family/takeaways-digital-detox/">See Full Breakdown &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
</style>
